cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CL, cs.CR

The paper proposes a new algorithm for learning grammar-based decision trees (GBDTs) for the interpretable classification and categorization of heterogeneous multivariate time series data. This work involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for data analysis and interpretation. The use of a context-free grammar for branching in GBDTs also involves formal language theory (cs.DM) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the application of GBDTs to analyze near mid-air collisions (NMACs) involves computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) as it relates to the development of the next-generation Airborne Collision Avoidance System (ACAS X).
